[2]
Date: Sat 28 May 2011
Source: bdnews24.com [edited]
http://bdnews24.com/pdetails.php?id=196917


Eight more people have been found infected with anthrax at Shahjadpur
and Ullapara upazilas in Sirajganj, taking the toll to 24 in the
district.

On Friday [27 May 2011], 16 people, including 3 children, were found
anthrax-positive in Shahjadpur upazila, only weeks after this year's
[2011] 1st outbreak was reported in Sathia, Pabna. Resident physician
of Ullapara Upazila Health Complex Dr Sukumar Roy told bdnews24.com on
Saturday [28 May 2011] that the infected patients had been given
antibiotics. Of the infected patients, 5 are from Mohanpur union
council of Ullahpara Upazila and the other 3 from Kayempur union
council of Shahjadpur Upazila. They received treatment at Ullapara
Upazila Health Complex, as both Mohanpur and Kayempur are neighbouring
union councils. "A medical team is working to scrutinise whether there
are any more patients in the area," the physician added.

Sirajganj district livestock officer Shafiqul Islam told bdnews24.com
that a buffalo was slaughtered in the areas, and those who processed
and consumed the meat got infected with anthrax. "All the cattle of
the villages in the upazila are being vaccinated to avoid recurrence
of last year [2010]-like spread of the epidemic," the livestock
officer added.

--
