ProMED-mail <promed@promedmail.org>

******
[3]
Date: Sun 29 May 2011
Source: The Daily Star [edited]
http://www.thedailystar.net/newDesign/latest_news.php?nid=30032


Six more people have been diagnosed with anthrax in Shahjadpur and
Ullapara upazilas of Sirajganj, the district civil surgeon confirmed
on Sunday [29 May 2011].

The infected are one person of Chak Haripur village, one of Kuti
Satbaria village and 2 of Gugibari village in Shahjadpur upazila, and
2 of Mohanpur Nada village in Ullapara upazila. Three persons became
ill as they processed meat of sick cows a few days back, District
Civil Surgeon Dr Najimuddin Khan said. One was infected after he
slaughtered a sick goat and sold the meat among the locals recently,
reports our Sirajganj correspondent, quoting the civil surgeon. Thana
Health Officer Dr Abdul Awal of Shahjadpur confirmed that 2 were
infected after eating the meat of a sick goat.

The civil surgeon of the district said that medical teams went to the
villages of the upazilas and gave antibiotic treatment to the infected
people.

A total of 30 people have been detected with the disease in the 2
upazilas since Friday [27 May 2011].

--
Communicated by:
ProMED-mail <promed@promedmail.org>

[This is going to be as bad as 2010. The 610 figure quoted for 2010
ignores the cases that occurred earlier in that year. Members will
have noted that all these reports were initiated by secondary human
cases. The Bangladesh livestock service needs to get ahead of the
curve. - Mod.MHJ]
